					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12138043#post-4291101</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12138043/carroll-280-r-01221#post-4291101</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 25 Jun 2019 16:24:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I find this article to be frustrating in almost the exact same way as the other part of this article duo but for different reasons. There’s fantastic imagery in stuffing people into barrels, you can really hear a great Chicago mobster voice in your head, and lines like the guns disappearing and “can be used to get rid of other problems.” are fantastic.</p> <p>But it falls flat on the ending. The whole piece feels like it’s building up for a report or log or something where a mobster goes into the Factory, but it never comes. A fantastic setup for a killer payload that never lands.</p> <p>I’m sad that I can’t bring myself to upvote these as I like both entries, but I feel like I’d be doing you both a disservice if I didn’t wait to give that upvote to the very best version these articles can be, which they are so close to and I know that both of you are capable of creating.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
